      "message": "Thanks. Apologize for the long comment. So is this the right sequence for an MP SP?\n\n1) During boot, the primary SPMC EC will call into SPMD through IMPDEF means to set entry point of SPMC secondary EC\u0027s(MP, non-migratable). SPMC secondary EC\u0027s are not initialized yet.\n\n2) During SPMC initialization, SPMC initializes primary EC\u0027s for each SP and enters it. The SP\u0027s primary EC will call into SPMC using SET_ENTRY_POINT(or some custom interface) or PSCI_CPU_ON(Secure world specialized call), to set the entry point for it\u0027s secondary EC\u0027s(MP, non-migratable). SP\u0027s secondary EC\u0027s are not yet initialized.\n\n3) Each SP\u0027s primary EC\u0027s yield to SPMC once init is done through MSG_WAIT/YIELD/whatever other message.\n\n4) SPMC primary EC yields to SPMD once init is done through MSG_WAIT/YIELD/whatever other message.\n\n5) NWd boots.\n\n6) When NWd wants to turn on secondary physical core, it uses PSCI_CPU_ON. EL3 on handler dispatches to SPMD and SPMD initializes SPMD EC corresponding to this PE and uses entry point provided earlier to enter SPMC. SPMC calls into all SP using SP EC corresponding to this PE. SP EC yields to SPMC using MSG_WAIT/YIELD/etc and SPMC yields to SPMD using the same messages.\n\n7) To run a particular SP EC, NWd executes FFA_MSG_SEND_DIRECT_REQ on a particular PE.",
